com.percussion.search.objectstore
Class PSWSSearchField

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.search.objectstore.PSWSSearchField

public class PSWSSearchField
extends Object

Class to represent the SearchField element of the document created from a PSWSSearchRequest object. See toXml(Document) for more information. Instances of this class are immutable after construction.

public static final String[] OP_ATTR_VALUES
Enumeration of the string representation of the OP_ATTR_xxx constants, used when serialized to XML. Each constant value is an index into this array of its string representation. This array must be modified as operator constants are added, modified, or removed.

Constructor Detail

PSWSSearchField

public PSWSSearchField(String name,
                       int op,
                       String value,
                       int connector)
Construct a field using an internal operator.

Parameters:
name - The name of the field, may not be null or empty.
op - The operator to use, must be one of the OP_ATTR_XXX values.
value - The value of the field, may not be null.
connector - The connector used to specify the logical operand used to connect this field with the next field within a list. Must be one of the CONN_ATTR_XXX values.

PSWSSearchField

public PSWSSearchField(String name,
                       String extOp,
                       String value,
                       int connector)
Construct a field using an external operator. Same as this(name, op, value, connector) but the op parameter is replaced with the extOp parameter described below.

Parameters:
extOp - The external operator to used, passed thru to the external search engine. May not be null or empty.

getOperator

public int getOperator()
Deprecated. use getOperatorEnum() instead.

Get the internal operator supplied during construction. If one was not supplied, getExternalOperator() will return a non-empty value, and this value should be ignored, in which case OP_ATTR_EQUAL is returned by default. Otherwise this field should be used to query the internal search engine using this operator.

Returns:
One of the OP_ATTR_XXX values.

getExternalOperator

public String getExternalOperator()
Get the external operator supplied during construction. If one was not supplied, then an empty string is returned, and the value of getOperator() should be used to construct search criteria from this field.

Returns:
Never null, may be empty. If non-empty, this field should be used to query the external search engine.

getValue

The value, never null, may be empty.

isExternal

Determine if this field specifies an external operator.

Returns:
true if getExternalOperator() would return a non-empty value, false otherwise.
